tips.en: Sticks and rocks can be harvested by attacking trees and boulders. Some weapons are more effective than others.
Taking damage while caught in a snare frees you immediately.
You can destroy crafted traps by attacking them. Steel traps can only be destroyed using explosives.
Crafted Blowgun Darts apply a sickness wound will cuase you to vomit and become temporarily stunned.
Crafted Satchels and Backpacks can be used to craft armor.
Access the in-game menu for a full list of crafting recipes.
FUNC allows you to craft, open Blue Crates, and call in your Personal Airdrop. Earn FUNC through exploration, combat, and recycling items.
If you are killed during a team match, you can watch your teammate's back in spectate mode.
If your Stamina drops below 30%, your movement speed starts to slow.
In teams matches, your teammate is highlighted with a blue outline. Don't attack your teammate.
If you are struck by a melee attack while holding a ranged weapon, you will be disarmed.
You can craft additional ammo for ranged weapons (including firearms). Check the help screen for recipe details.
You can shoot an Airdrop to drop it faster.
Learn to recognize the different tiers of weapons. It is difficult to overcome a weapon tier disadvantage unless you are highly skilled.
You can use explosive barrels to make Crafted Explosives, but be careful, a well-placed arrow can detonate the barrel while you're crafting.
Practice carrying Crafted Caltrops or Smoke Bombs to help you escape dangerous encounters.
Watch your back. Blocking won't protect you against a backstab.
Activating a Poison Gas Vent can deter a chasing opponent.
If you trigger a Poison Gas Vent and the gas kills another player, you receive credit for the kill.
The Bait Crate Airdrop can be called for free and deals significant damage to anyone foolish enough to open it.
Shoving will stagger a blocking or charging opponent, making them vulnerable.
The Weakness wound reduces your damage output.
Explosives are dangerous not only for the damage they deal but the crippling wound they apply.
The remnants of past contestants are littered throughout the arena and provide FUNC if you discover them.
Blue Crates require FUNC to open and contain tier 3 weapons and items.
Friendly fire is always active. Be careful not to hit your teammate in cooperative matches.
A Man Tracker is equally useful for tracking down an opponent or avoiding a confrontation.
Teaming (except with your assigned teammate) is  prohibited. Violators will be punished.
Falls from high places will hurt and cripple you, but falling damage is not lethal.
Visit the Training Range to practice your combat skills and learn crafting recipes.
Any weapon or item can be recycled in exchange for FUNC. Recyling Stations are found at all buildings.
Running in a zig-zag fashion makes it difficult for a player to hit you with a bow or gun. The same principle applies to running from alligators.
Red Crates contain useful weapons and items, but require explosive damage to unlock them.
You can instantly trigger a Poison Gas Vent by dealing enough damage to it. Bows are well-suited for this task.
Green Crates are found throughout the arena, both in buildings and out in the open. They contain mid-tier weapons and items.
Crouching slows your movement significantly but makes you nearly silent and allows you to avoid triggering traps.
You can pay FUNC to restore health at the Med Stations found at every building.
You and your teammate will not trigger any traps that you place, which makes it easier to lure opponents into them.
Backpacks expand your inventory to its maximum size of five slots. Backpacks and Crafted Satchels do not stack.
Tactical Body Armor offers the best possible damage protection. It does not stack with Crafted Armor.
Killing other contestants is the fastest way to earn FUNC, but recycling scavenged items is safer.
Headshots from bows and firearms deal double damage.
Multiple Stims of the same type do not stack. Take one at a time.
Some bridges will collapse when damaged. You must activate the control console to reset them.
Your Stamina recovers at its maximum rate when you stand still and slightly slower while walking.
Moving through water is especially noisy.
Backstabs with melee weapons deal double damage.
Airdrops can be called multiple times per match.
You can be disarmed when you have a fully charged throw, so be careful when throwing melee weapons at close range.
